== Discussion

*Accuracy in joint kinematics*

Average joint position error generally tended to be under 30mm, with the lowest error in the medio-lateral direction and highest in the anterior-posterior direction. 

notes for comparison:
- Theia Markerless speeds for ankle, knee, and hip (in 3D) were 24, 22 and 36mm.
- Nakano MAEs were mostly under 30, some exceeding 40 (also generally higher MAE in Y than Z) for walking

